iagnostics","name":"area:diagnostics","color":"1d76db","default":false,"description":"Phase A: parser/eval errors, REPL, traces"},{"id":10795985541,"node_id":"LA_kwDOP9nMvc8AAAACg32qhQ","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-foundation/relative-meta-logic/labels/phase:A","name":"phase:A","color":"fbca04","default":false,"description":"Phase A: diagnostics and developer experience"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-04-26T20:32:02Z","updated_at":"2026-04-26T20:33:31Z","closed_at":null,"assignee":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Motivation\nComparison doc lists REPL as `Part` for RML. Lean/Rocq/Isabelle have first-class REPLs; users expect one for any modern proving system.\n\n## Goal\nA REPL that maintains a persistent `Env` between user inputs and prints diagnostics inline.\n\n## LiNo Surface\n```\nrml> (a: a is a)\nrml> ((a = a) has probability 1)\nrml> (? (a = a))\n1\n```\n\n## API Surface\n`rml repl` subcommand in both implementations.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] REPL preserves env across commands.\n- [ ] `:reset`, `:env`, `:load <file>`, `:save <file>` meta-commands.\n- [ ] Tab-completion of declared symbols (best-effort).\n- [ ] Tests cover state preservation and meta-commands.\n\n## References\n- Source case study: [`docs/case-studies/issue-26/`](https://github.com/link-foundation/relative-meta-logic/tree/main/docs/case-studies/issue-26)\n- Comparison docs: [CONCEPTS-COMPARISION.md](https://github.com/link-foundation/relative-meta-logic/blob/main/docs/CONCEPTS-COMPARISION.md), [FEATURE-COMPARISION.md](https://github.com/link-foundation/relative-meta-logic/blob/main/docs/FEATURE-COMPARISION.md)\n- Planning issue: #26\n\n## Dependencies\n- Depends on: #28\n- Blocks: #78\n\n## Out 