        "type": "text",
        "text": "So `await import(replUrl)` never resolves. That's actually surprising. The runRepl module imports `readline` and `node:fs`. Should work.\n\nHmm wait - let me check if it's because `rml-repl.mjs` itself imports `rml-links.mjs`, which is currently being loaded (ESM circular import). The CLI block in rml-links.mjs is being executed during its own module load, but rml-repl.mjs imports from rml-links.mjs which hasn't finished initializing because it's awaiting the dynamic import that's awaiting rml-links.mjs to complete.\n\nYES, that's it. Circular dependency. The `rml-repl.mjs` does `import { evaluate, Env, formatDiagnostic } from './rml-links.mjs';` which means when rml-links.mjs's CLI block awaits rml-repl.mjs, rml-repl.mjs awaits rml-links.mjs which is awaiting rml-repl.mjs... deadlock.\n\nSolution: Don't lazy-import; instead just import unconditionally at the top, OR move the CLI logic to a separate file that imports both. Let me just import unconditionally - the readline dep is in node:readline anyway, no real penalty."
