        "content": "62e712e5347d98f5700cc3155a982fbc761de212\nAdd structured diagnostics with source spans (issue #28)\n---\nReplace ad-hoc throw/panic error reporting with a structured Diagnostic\ntype carrying a stable error code, human-readable message, and 1-based\nsource span (file/line/col). Both implementations expose a new\n`evaluate()` entry point that returns `{ results, diagnostics }` so\ncallers (CLIs, editors, tooling) can surface failures without crashing.\n\n- JS: new `evaluate`, `Diagnostic`, `RmlError`, `formatDiagnostic`, and\n  `computeFormSpans` exports. Internal throw sites now use `RmlError`\n  with an error code; `evaluate()` catches them and attaches the\n  pre-computed form span.\n- Rust: new `evaluate`, `Diagnostic`, `Span`, `EvaluateResult`,\n  `format_diagnostic`, and `compute_form_spans` exports. Internal panics\n  in the evaluator are caught via `catch_unwind`, mapped to error codes\n  by inspecting the panic payload, and packaged as diagnostics. The\n  default panic hook is silenced for the duration of the call so stack\n  traces never leak to stderr.\n- Both CLIs now print `<file>:<line>:<col>: <CODE>: <message>` plus the\n  source line and a caret under the offending column, and exit non-zero\n  whenever any diagnostic is emitted.\n- New tests in `js/tests/diagnostics.test.mjs` (11 cases) and\n  `rust/tests/diagnostics_tests.rs` (10 cases) cover E001/E002/E004/E006\n  triggers, span correctness across blank lines, and CLI formatting.\n- New `docs/DIAGNOSTICS.md` lists every code with its trigger and\n  documents the API; ARCHITECTURE.md and README.md cross-link to it.\n\nThe existing `run()` entry points and 657 pre-existing tests remain\nunchanged: the diagnostics surface is purely additive.\n\n===",
