        "type": "tool_use",
        "id": "toolu_01Bpgzge9NZQvVeZ4U1u7SVY",
        "name": "Bash",
        "input": {
          "command": "git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nAdd interactive REPL with persistent env (issue #29)\n\nAdd a `rml repl` subcommand to both implementations.  The REPL maintains\na persistent `Env` between user inputs so users can declare terms,\nattach probabilities, and query the resulting state across many lines.\nDiagnostics from issue #28 are reported inline; LiNo input that errors\nout does not lose any earlier successful results.\n\nMeta-commands (start with `:`):\n  :help / :?      show the help text\n  :reset          discard all state and start a fresh Env\n  :env            print declared terms / assignments / types / lambdas\n                  / valence / range / user-set symbol priors\n  :load <file>    evaluate a `.lino` file in the current Env\n  :save <file>    write the session transcript (as `.lino`) to <file>\n  :quit / :exit   exit the REPL (also Ctrl-D)\n\nBest-effort tab-completion offers known meta-commands when the line\nstarts with `:`, and otherwise built-in keywords plus identifiers\ndeclared in the env (terms, ops, symbol priors, lambda names).\n\n- JS: new `js/src/rml-repl.mjs` exporting `Repl`, `runRepl`,\n  `formatEnv`, `makeCompleter`, `envCompletionCandidates`, and\n  `HELP_TEXT`.  `evaluate()` in `rml-links.mjs` now accepts an existing\n  `Env` so the REPL can thread state through each line.  The CLI was\n  refactored into an async `runCli()` helper to avoid a top-level\n  await deadlock when dynamically importing the REPL module.\n- Rust: new `rust/src/repl.rs` exposing `Repl`, `ReplStep`,\n  `format_env`, and `run_repl`.  `lib.rs` adds `evaluate_with_env`\n  alongside the existing `evaluate` entry point.  `main.rs` dispatches\n  the `repl` subcommand and suppresses the prompt when stdin is not a\n  TTY so piped input stays clean.\n- Tests: 20 cases in `js/tests/repl.test.mjs` and 21 cases in\n  `rust/tests/repl_tests.rs` cover state preservation across feeds,\n  every meta-command (including `:load`/`:save` round-trips against\n  real files), tab-completion, and the full `run_repl` driver.  All\n  existing tests (444 JS, 244 Rust) still pass.\n\nEOF\n)\"",
          "description": "Commit REPL implementation"
        },
        "caller": {
          "type": "direct"
        }
      }
    ],
